# Matrix Multiplication Scaling Study (IKJ Order)

## Objective

Study how execution time changes as matrix size increases while keeping the algorithm fixed.

The implementation used:

```c
for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
    for (int k = 0; k < N; k++) {
        int r = A[i][k];

        for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
            C[i][j] += A[i][k] * B[k][j];
        }
    }
}
```

Characteristics:

* Loop Order: IKJ
* Row-major storage (C language)
* Matrix type: `int`
* Three matrices: A, B, C
* Execution time measured using `clock_gettime()`

